# Web Crawler

## Prerequisites

Before using the Web Crawler, ensure you have the following installed on your machine:

- Node.js: [Download and install Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)

## After node.js installation we need to follow below steps

To use the Web Crawler, follow these steps:

Open a project. In my case i have used VS-Code

## Installation

npm install

## Run

Open terminal and navigate to src folder.. and then

Run the following command:

npx ts-node index.ts <url> <depth>

url example : any for your choice

depth example : should be an number 1 , 2 ,3 etc

# Addtional dependencies

npm install -g ts-node
npm i --save-dev @types/node-fetch
